Introduction

QWER (translated to Favorite Children) is a South Korean four-member project girl band under 3Y CORPORATION and Tamago Production. The companies are both founded by YouTuber and CEO Kim Egg, otherwise known as Kim Gye-ran. They made their official debut on October 18, 2023, with the single album "Harmony From Discord".

On July 2, 2023, Tamago Production announced that they will be debuting a four-member project girl band on their YouTube channel. At the time, only drummer Chodan had been recruited, while the other members were still being recruited. Eventually, they were revealed through their YouTube pre-debut series "OSHI NO KO Project" where they chose Twitch streamer Magenta as their bassist, internet personality Hina as their keyboardist, and former member of J-Pop group NMB48 Lee Siyeon as their vocalist and guitarist. By August 2023, the members were assembled and began training and preparing for their debut.

On September 24, QWER announced that they would make their official debut with the single "Harmony From Discord". On March 14, 2024, QWER released a comeback poster for their first mini album "Manito" which was released on April 1.
